Q: How to contain a label into its preceeding expanded element, without using a wrapper container? A: <p>You can simplify the HTML, use a pseudo-element as a box, and do some flex styling on hover.</p>
<p><div class="snippet" data-lang="js" data-hide="false" data-console="true" data-babel="false" data-babel-preset-react="false" data-babel-preset-ts="false">
<div class="snippet-code">
<pre class="snippet-code-css lang-css prettyprint-override"><code>:root {
  --background-color: yellow;
}

h3 {
  box-sizing: border-box;
  display: flex;
  width: 100%;

  &amp;::before {
    content: '';
    display: block;
    width: 25px;
    height: 22px;
    background-color: var(--background-color);
  }

  &amp;:hover {
    align-items: end;
    justify-content: end;
    background-color: var(--background-color);
    height: 100px;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    padding: 0.5rem;

    &amp;::before {
      display: none;
    }
  }
}</code></pre>
<pre class="snippet-code-html lang-html prettyprint-override"><code>&lt;h3&gt;Yellow&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Bla, bla, bla&lt;/p&gt;</code></pre>
</div>
</div>
</p>

Q: Codeigniter active record where() with serialize data and regex A: <p>Your <code>where()</code> requires some tweaks because the <code>REGEXP</code> SQL keyword is being treated as a PHP constant and it needs to be written after the column name in the first parameter of the method call.</p>
<p>Also your query builder script can be simplified to return the count as an integer.</p>
<pre class="lang-php prettyprint-override"><code>public function countSessionsByUser(int $userId): int
{
    return $this-&gt;db
        -&gt;where(
            'user_data REGEXP',
            's:7:&quot;user_id&quot;;s:[0-9]+:&quot;' . $userId . '&quot;;',
            false // I don't know if this parameyer is actually necessary
        )
        -&gt;count_all_results(SESSIONS_TABLE);
}
</code></pre>

Q: file reader read blob file A: <p>Check how to use blob <a href="http://qnimate.com/an-introduction-to-javascript-blobs-and-file-interface/" rel="nofollow noreferrer">here</a> it is clearly explained and it should be enough to get you going.</p>

<p>Try this: 
Assuming that <code>file:///C:/blob.blb</code> exists and you are sure, then do it like so:</p>

<pre><code>    imageOut.addEventListener('load', () =&gt; {
        const reader = new FileReader();
        var f = File.createFromFileName("file:///C:/blob.blb");
        reader.addEventListener('load', (e) =&gt; {
              const arrayBuffer = reader.readAsArrayBuffer(f);

            global.blob = new Blob([arrayBuffer], { type: f.type});

        });
// notice this is outside the reader Load.

var intval = setInterval(function(){
      if(blob !== undefined){
         imageOut.src = URL.createObjectURL(blob);  
         clearInterval(intval);
      }
     }, 100);

    });
</code></pre>

<p>I hope it helps.</p>
